{
  "texts": [
    "Delegated act on auditing procedures and methodologiesOn October 20, 2023, the European Commission published a delegated act to provide a framework guiding VLOPs and very large online search engines (VLOSEs) in performing audits mandated under Article 37 of the DSA [50].",
    "The act specifies several procedural rules and audit templates:• Requires using a \"reasonable assurance\" audit standard entailing high confidence in assessing compliance (Annex I).• Mandates reporting audit risk analysis before conducting procedures (Article 9).",
    "• Requires outlining planned procedures, evidence sources, and sampling methods (Article 10).",
    "• Stipulates providing compliance conclusions for each audited DSA obligation as positive, positive with comments, or negative (Article 8).",
    "• Offers guidance on assessing novel DSA provisions around risk assessments (Article 13), risk mitigation (Article 14), crisis response (Article 15), and auditing itself (Article 16)."
  ]
}